President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday inaugurated the National Economic Council (NEC), for the next four years. Buhari, however, urged the state governments to deepen collaboration with the Federal government on security among other things. Buhari via his Twitter page said “Today I inaugurated the National Economic Council (NEC), for the next four years. The Federal and State Governments must deepen collaboration on security, education, health and agriculture, to make a difference in the lives of our people”    